<TITLE> BNP's Huda, AL's Mollah get bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 7 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Wednesday granted bail to the former communication minister in the BNP government, Nazmul Huda, in two corruption cases. Justices Md. Muzammel Hossain and Md. Afzal Hossain Ahmed of a bench passed the orders upon hearing two separate bail petition filed by Huda. Azmalul Hossain moved the bail applications for Huda, himself a lawyer. Another bench of justices Mirza Hossain Haider and Borhan Uddin granted three months' interim bail to newly-elected Awami League lawmaker Habibur Rahman Mollah in a tax evasion case. The court also issued the government to explain why he should not be enlarged on regular bail on a petition moved by Bazlur Rahman. b
